Name: ACTIVE
OwnerComment: The value of the {term:Data Entity} that is engaging.

Name: INACTIVE
OwnerComment: The value of the {term:Data Entity} that is not engaging.

Name: AVAILABLE
OwnerComment: The value or status of an XML element when it is available.

Name: UNAVAILABLE
OwnerComment: The value of the {term:Data Entity} either when the data is not received or the entity is incapable of providing data.

Name: TANDEM
OwnerComment: Elements are physically connected to each other and operate as a single unit.

Name: SYNCHRONOUS
OwnerComment: Physical or logical parts which are not physically connected to each other but are operating together.

Name: MASTER
OwnerComment: It provides information or state values that influences the operation of other {model:DataItem} of similar type.

Name: SLAVE
OwnerComment: The axis is a slave to the {model:COUPLED_AXES}

Name: HOME
OwnerComment: The component at its home position.

Name: TRAVEL
OwnerComment: The component is in motion.

Name: PARKED
OwnerComment: The component has been moved to a fixed position.

Name: STOPPED
OwnerComment: The component is stopped.

Name: OPEN
OwnerComment: A component is open to the point of a positive confirmation.

Name: CLOSED
OwnerComment: A component is closed to the point of a positive confirmation.

Name: UNLATCHED
OwnerComment: An intermediate position.

Name: AUTOMATIC
OwnerComment: The {model:Controller} is configured to automatically execute a program.

Name: MANUAL
OwnerComment: Operations based on the instructions received from an external source.

Name: MANUAL_DATA_INPUT
OwnerComment: The operator can enter a series of operations for the controller to perform.

Name: SEMI_AUTOMATIC
OwnerComment: The controller  executes a single set of instructions from an active program and then stops until given a command to execute the next set of instructions.

Name: EDIT
OwnerComment: The controller is currently functioning as a programming device and is not capable of executing an active program.

Name: ON
OwnerComment: On state or value.

Name: OFF
OwnerComment: Off state or value.

Name: ARMED
OwnerComment: The emergency stop circuit is complete and the piece of equipment, component, or composition element is allowed to operate.

Name: TRIGGERED
OwnerComment: The operation of the piece of equipment, component, or composition element is inhibited.

Name: YES
OwnerComment: The {model:END_OF_BAR} has been reached.

Name: NO
OwnerComment: The {model:END_OF_BAR} has not been reached.

Name: READY
OwnerComment: A component is ready to engage.

Name: ACTIVE
OwnerComment: The value of the {term:Data Entity} that is engaging.

Name: INTERRUPTED
OwnerComment: The action of a {model:Component} has been suspended due to an external signal.

Name: FEED_HOLD
OwnerComment: Motion of a {model:Component} has been commanded to stop at its current position.

Name: STOPPED
OwnerComment: The component is stopped.

Name: OPTIONAL_STOP
OwnerComment: The controllers program has been intentionally stopped

Name: PROGRAM_STOPPED
OwnerComment: The execution of the {model:Controller}'s program has been stopped by a command from within the program.

Name: PROGRAM_COMPLETED
OwnerComment: The execution of the controllers program has been stopped by a command from within the program.

Name: PRODUCTION
OwnerComment: A {term:Structural Element} is currently producing product.

Name: SETUP
OwnerComment: A {term:Structural Element} is being prepared or modified to begin production of product.

Name: TEARDOWN
OwnerComment: Typically, a {term:Structural Element} has completed the production of a product and is being modified or returned to a neutral state such that it may then be prepared to begin production of a different product.

Name: MAINTENANCE
OwnerComment: Action related to maintenance on the piece of equipment.

Name: PROCESS_DEVELOPMENT
OwnerComment: A {term:Structural Element} is being used to prove-out a new process.

Name: ENABLED
OwnerComment: A component is currently operational and performing as expected.

Name: DISABLED
OwnerComment: A component is currently not operational.

Name: INDEPENDENT
OwnerComment: The path is operating independently and without the influence of another path.

Name: MASTER
OwnerComment: It provides information or state values that influences the operation of other {model:DataItem} of similar type.

Name: SYNCHRONOUS
OwnerComment: Physical or logical parts which are not physically connected to each other but are operating together.

Name: MIRROR
OwnerComment: The axes associated with the path are mirroring the motion of the {model:MASTER} path.

Name: ACTIVE
OwnerComment: The value of the {term:Data Entity} that is engaging.

Name: READY
OwnerComment: A component is ready to engage.

Name: NOT_READY
OwnerComment: A component is not ready to engage.

Name: SPINDLE
OwnerComment: The axis is functioning as a spindle.

Name: INDEX
OwnerComment: The axis is configured to index.

Name: CONTOUR
OwnerComment: The position of the axis is being interpolated.
